description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Are you a Treatment Room/Practice Nurse who wants to enjoy the full range of Practice Nurse duties, such as immunisations, wound management and health screening whilst building good relationship with our diverse patients? If yes, then this could be the role for you! This excellent surgery is seeking a Treatment Room/ Practice Nurse to come in and enjoy a wide variety of responsibilities, that will keep things very interesting from day to day. &lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;About us:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We are a long established practice operating from 3 sites across Ilkeston with patient list of circa 15,000&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We value caring and high-quality care for our patients and support for one another&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Our clinical staff comprises friendly, supportive partners, salaried GPs, a clinical pharmacist, ANPs, skilled nursing and HCA team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Clinicians are supported by effective administrative team with strong management&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We are Training and Nottingham University Teaching Practice&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We were rated Good by CQC in all areas&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We are high QOF achievers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We use TPP SystmOne clinical system &lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The Benefits:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Supportive partnership&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt; A very diverse role&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support in professional development&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Competitive salary and benefits package &lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;About you- we are looking for a person who is:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt; Flexible and a good team worker.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Enthusiastic, forward thinking and a motivator.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Confident and able to work under pressure.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Self-aware and understanding of own limitations and those of others.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;An effective mentor and communicator&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Committed to ongoing professional and practice development.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;br /&gt; Your Role:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;20-25 hours a week; to be worked over 3-4 days during opening hours of 8.30-18.30&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt; provides opportunity to make a positive change to our diverse community&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Combine teamwork with autonomy in decision making, within the remit of the role &lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Qualifications Essential:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;span&gt; • Full registration with NMC- minimum of 6 months &lt;br /&gt; • Experience of working in accordance with the NMC Code of Professional Conduct ( 2002 and The Scope of Professional Practice ( 1992 )&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; • Competency in basic nursing duties required for the post&lt;br /&gt; • Excellent communication and interpersonal skills&lt;br /&gt; • Ability to work well autonomously and within a team&lt;br /&gt; • Excellent timekeeping skills&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Qualification and experience in management of INR clinics or willingness to undertake necessary training will be an advantage. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;We welcome informal visits. To  arrange one, please contact either Anna Bednarska, Business Practice Manager or Wenda Cannon, Lead PN on 0115 930 1105. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
